Text.Value: He needs me to complete the ritual. He'll be furious if you stop me from joining him.
Isn't it obvious? I'm going to kill Cazador.
You tortured us. For days at a time.
Godey will not disobey the master, much less for someone like you.
You always were sharp, little one. Sharp enough to cut yourself.
Attack.
Oh yes, and you sang so sweetly for me. None of the others screamed like you did.
After all these years, you still think you can lie to me? Shame on you.
But master called me home! I have to get to him!
Take it and go. Impudent little brat.
Oh no. No no no, Godey is not worried by your threats. Godey knows just how to break you.
I'm looking for Cazador. Where is he?
Hah! No no, it is too late. The doors are sealed on master's orders.
Don't be mad at Godey, child. I only did my job. Only kept you in line.
Here, here it is.
So so, you've come home, little one. And come to visit Godey in your old kennel.
How about I start breaking bones and keep going until I find that key?
Now, let's hear that scream of yours one last time.
Isn't it obvious? I'm here to kill Cazador.
You're too late, the master entered the ballroom and ordered the doors be sealed behind him. They are not to be opened until his business is done.
Godey will not let you get away with blasphemy. Godey will see you punished!
It seems I need to put you in your place one last time. Then you're the master's.
Godey was wondering about that... Godey knows the master was searching for Astarion. He must have forgotten Astarion was lost.
But you're too late, the master entered the ballroom and had me seal the doors behind him. They will not to be opened until his business is done.
Hah! You think you can hurt Godey? Oh no, you have been away for too long.
Come little one, let's hear that scream of yours one more time.
Now go to him. Help him achieve his destiny.
How dare you! As if you could lay a finger on the master, you ungrateful little brat!
The doors are locked for a reason - master ordered it so. Master ordered they not be opened, so locked they shall remain.
Godey will not let you get away with blasphemy. Godey will see you punished!
We're here to see the master, but the ballroom door's locked. Give us the key.

EditorData.NodeContext: reluctantly calling Cazador 'the master' to try and trick Godey into giving you the key

Text.Value: Family or not, the master will be obeyed! You will not open that door.
*This playground belonged to Godey - a skeleton sadistic enough that Cazador left him in charge of 'discipling' you and the other vampire spawn.*
Godey will not open them for anyone, much less for you.
How dare you! As if you could lay a finger on the master, you ungrateful little brat!
The ballroom door's locked and I need the key.
The master will not be disobeyed! You will not open that door.
You always were sharp, little one. Sharp enough to cut yourself.
I've come home to rejoin the family.
I was hoping you'd say that. Taking it from the ruins of your corpse will be more satisfying anyway.
You can try, little one, but you will fail.
I do want to hurt you, if that's what you mean.
It's taking everything I have not to grind your rotten carcass to dust.
What are you doing here? Did you miss me as I've missed you?
*The familiar stink of the cell fills your nostrils and memories flood back. You remember spending days, tendays, locked down here in 'the Kennel', suffering endless tortures.*
But if you're not here to see Godey, why are you here, little one?
Wait! Godey has the key. Godey can give it to you.
I know you're there, Godey. Stop skulking and show yourself.
Remembering the good times, little one?
He needs me to complete the ritual. He'll be furious if you stop me from joining him.
Remembering how you'd sing for Godey? Oh, but I have missed your screams.
Perhaps. You did come home... Yes, you can be trusted. It is a family key, after all.
No no, master will be furious if it is lost. Godey must find it.
Here, here it - no... where is it?
But master called me home! I have to get to him!
*The very same skeleton you catch trying to sneak up on you now.*
Oh yes, fight Godey. Spill your blood on his kennel's floor.

Synopsis:
Origing Moment with Godey, lackey of Cazador.
Astarion hates him.
